name: Krajete
businessDescription: Krajete delivers innovative NOx reduction systems and NOx control technologies designed to capture and valorise emissions across industries. By using nature-inspired methods like adsorber-based purification and advanced bioprocesses, we help clients go beyond compliance. Our scalable NOx removal solutions serve as a powerful alternative to SCR systems, enabling businesses to transform harmful emissions into valuable materials. Whether tackling regulatory pressure or seeking sustainable innovation, Krajete supports a cleaner future by turning NOx into opportunity.
tags: carbon capture, nox control, nox removal, cleantech
longBusinessDescription:
Krajete delivers NOx reduction systems and NOx control technologies that let industrial sites meet ultra-low emission limits without the cost and complexity of catalytic processes such as SCR or SNCR. By capturing pollutants instead of burning or dosing them away, our skid-mounted equipment runs at low temperatures and eliminates the need for ammonia, urea or precious-metal catalysts—cutting energy use, preventing ammonia slip and slashing maintenance. That means fast compliance with the tougher caps set by the EU’s revised Industrial Emissions Directive, the U.S. EPA’s Good Neighbor Plan and the EU 2024 National Emission Reduction Commitments report.
Our modular adsorber slots straight into the exhaust line, first trapping NOx and, with interchangeable cartridges, also removing SOx and bulk CO₂. A short, low-grade-heat pulse regenerates the bed in place, extending adsorbent life over thousands of cycles and keeping downtime to a minimum. When carbon pricing bites, the same platform accepts an optional biomethanation reactor that blends captured CO₂ with green hydrogen to yield pipeline-grade methane, turning a disposal cost into a revenue-ready fuel.
These results rest on two core strengths: tailored adsorption materials tuned for selective, high-efficiency capture and microbiology that transforms waste gases into valuable molecules. Deployed across power generation, waste-to-energy, chemicals, mobility testing and marine engines, our solutions consistently achieve single-digit-ppm NOx with predictable operating costs—giving clients one trusted supplier for air compliance, carbon valorisation and fuel resilience.
Engagement is straightforward. We take a gas sample, run a detailed analysis and performance simulation, then issue a guaranteed removal figure with a fixed service schedule. Once approved, the same engineers design, build and install the skid, train plant staff and activate remote monitoring so results stay transparent. The outcome is assured compliance, lower OPEX than SCR/SNCR and a clear path to monetise captured carbon—delivered under a single contract with Krajete.

- Full privacy: Your location data is protected with end-to-end encryption and never leaves your device in plain text, ensuring only those you explicitly authorize can access your whereabouts.
- Based in EU: Enjoy the highest level of data protection under strict GDPR compliance, with everything working exclusively within the European Union.
Use Case
Paralino is a perfect family safety tool, it keeps your loved ones connected without any privacy drawbacks. It is a great travel tracker allowing you to share your location during trips and outdoor activities. You can also use it solo as a personal phone finder and easily locate and track your own devices.

Artypa addresses the limitations of fragmented AI tool ecosystems by offering a unified platform for accessing diverse AI functionalities.

Key Features:

- Consolidation: Access a wide range of AI tools within a single, user-friendly interface.
- Efficiency: Streamline workflows and minimize context switching between disparate services.
- Flexibility: A credit-based system with one-time billing provides users with granular control over costs.

Artypa empowers users to explore and leverage the power of AI without the constraints of multiple subscriptions.
tags: AI Content, AI Productivity, AI Generation
longBusinessDescription:
Traditional AI workflows often involve navigating a plethora of disparate platforms, leading to inefficiencies, cognitive overload, and increased operational costs. Artypa mitigates these challenges by consolidating a diverse range of AI functionalities within a single, unified platform. 
Key features of the Artypa platform include:
- Unified Access: Seamlessly access a comprehensive suite of AI tools, including text generation, image creation, data analysis, and more, all within a single, intuitive interface.
- Credit-Based Consumption: A flexible credit-based system replaces traditional subscriptions. Users purchase credits upfront and consume them as needed, optimizing resource allocation and minimizing unnecessary expenditures.
- Enhanced Efficiency: Streamline workflows, reduce cognitive friction, and improve overall productivity by eliminating the need to constantly switch between different AI platforms.
- Scalability and Customization: The Artypa platform is designed to scale with user needs, offering customizable features and the ability to integrate with existing business workflows.
By adopting Artypa, organizations can:
- Reduce operational costs: Eliminate the need for multiple subscriptions and associated administrative overhead.
- Improve employee productivity: Streamline workflows and empower employees with a unified AI toolkit.
- Foster innovation: Encourage experimentation and exploration of new AI capabilities within a controlled and cost-effective environment.
- Gain a competitive advantage: Leverage the power of AI to optimize business processes and achieve superior outcomes.
Artypa is currently under active development, with ongoing efforts focused on expanding the platform's capabilities and integrating with a wider range of enterprise applications.

name: Share your Party
businessDescription:
Share Your Party is an innovative app that simplifies event planning and participation. It connects organizers with attendees, offering tools for seamless event creation, ticket sales, and real-time updates. With personalized event recommendations, sustainable practices like digital tickets, and features like rideshare coordination, we make every event effortless and eco-friendly. 

Starting in Austria and expanding across Europe, our scalable platform aims to transform how people connect and celebrate. Whether you’re hosting a private party or a public festival, Share Your Party is your go-to solution for successful, memorable events.
tags: party, event planning, social community, app
longBusinessDescription:
Share Your Party is a dynamic platform designed to transform the way events are planned, promoted, and experienced. The app bridges the gap between event organizers and participants, offering a streamlined and user-friendly interface that caters to both personal gatherings and large-scale public events. With its emphasis on simplicity, sustainability, and scalability, Share Your Party redefines the event management landscape.
Core Features and Offerings
The platform provides organizers with intuitive tools to create, manage, and promote their events efficiently. Key features include:
Event Listing and Management: Easy setup and customization of events, including descriptions, schedules, and images.
Ticket Sales and Payment Integration: Secure and seamless payment options for attendees, with multiple payment methods like credit cards, PayPal, and instant transfers.
Real-Time Updates: Notifications and updates for attendees about event changes or important announcements.
Participant Engagement: Options for attendees to communicate, form groups, and organize rideshares to events.
Analytics for Organizers: Insights into ticket sales, attendance forecasts, and user engagement to optimize future events.
Participants benefit from personalized event recommendations based on their preferences and location, ensuring a tailored experience that maximizes event discovery and engagement.
Sustainability and Innovation
Share Your Party is committed to promoting sustainable practices in the event industry. By digitizing event management processes, the app reduces the need for physical tickets, flyers, and other paper materials. It encourages efficient resource use and minimizes environmental impact, making it a forward-thinking solution for the modern world.
Revenue Model
The business operates on a tiered commission system, where fees are applied to ticketed events based on ticket price ranges:
For tickets priced at €1–50, a 5% fee for organizers and a 4% fee for participants are applied.
For tickets priced at €100–200, the fees decrease slightly to 4% for organizers and 3% for participants.
Additional revenue streams include:
Premium Listings: Organizers can pay for featured placement of their events on the platform.
Subscription Plans: Regular organizers can subscribe for reduced fees and added benefits.
Data Insights Services: Providing organizers with advanced analytics for a fee.
Market and Expansion
Initially launching in Austria, Share Your Party targets university students, local communities, and established event organizers. The expansion plan includes targeting major European event hubs such as Berlin, Amsterdam, and Ibiza, focusing on vibrant social and cultural hubs to build a loyal user base.
Vision and Mission
The vision of Share Your Party is to become the leading platform for seamless, sustainable, and engaging event experiences. Its mission is to empower organizers and attendees by providing innovative tools that simplify event planning, foster community connections, and promote eco-friendly practices.
Future Outlook
With its scalable business model, user-centric design, and commitment to sustainability, Share Your Party is poised to disrupt the event management industry. By addressing the needs of organizers and participants alike, the platform creates a mutually beneficial ecosystem that ensures long-term success and growth in both local and international markets.

name: Wedding Capsule
businessDescription: A Digital wedding guestbook for messages, photos, videos, and memories
tags: Wedding & Event Planning, Lifestyle, Productivity, Personal Life, Wedding Guest book
longBusinessDescription:
Wedding Capsule is a modern digital guestbook and memory collection tool that replaces traditional guestbooks with an interactive, all-in-one solution. It collects heartfelt messages, photos, videos, and voice recordings from guests, organizing them into a dynamic timeline. Guests can easily participate using QR codes and familiar platforms like WhatsApp, Facebook Messenger, or a web browser—no app download required.
Key Features:
- Interactive Guestbook: Guests share messages, photos, videos, and voice notes, creating a complete memory collection.
- Real-Time Timeline: All contributions appear instantly in a beautiful, organized timeline.
- Effortless Access: Custom-designed QR codes, placed on invitations, menus, or table cards, provide instant guest access.
- WhatsApp and Messenger Integration: Guests can contribute using platforms they already know, making it easy for everyone.
- Post-Wedding Reminders: Automated follow-ups ensure guests upload any additional photos and videos.
- Fun Photo and Video Missions: Creative tasks like “Take a selfie with the couple!” make participation engaging and fun.
Benefits:
Wedding Capsule solves the chaos of collecting wedding memories by centralizing them in one place. Couples receive a complete keepsake that includes messages, photos, and even emotional voice notes. Photo and video missions create unique moments, while the platform’s simplicity ensures even less tech-savvy guests can contribute effortlessly.
How It Works:
- Setup: Couples customize QR codes matching their wedding theme and place them on invitations, menus, or at the venue.
- During the Wedding: Guests scan the QR codes to access the guestbook and share memories instantly via WhatsApp, Messenger, or browser.
- After the Wedding: Automated reminders prompt guests to upload additional photos and videos they may have missed.
- The Final Keepsake: All contributions are organized into a downloadable timeline, preserving the wedding’s full story.
Wedding Capsule is more than a guestbook—it’s a memory collection system that turns your wedding into a timeless keepsake. From heartfelt messages to funny videos, it captures every angle of your special day. Perfect for modern couples, it ensures no moment is missed.

We offer live classes taught by real people, where people teach a subject because they care and know a lot about it.  On PassionClass, years of experience matter more than almost anything else.  
PassionClass is truly the best place on earth to learn a language.  Duolingo sounds great, but do you know anyone who’s actually learned to speak from an app?  You need classes, group energy, and human connection to get immersed in a language- an opportunity to come and share and exchange and experience, which is what language is truly about.  Our platform fosters this immersive experience, where learners benefit from the dynamic energy of group classes and forge meaningful human connections essential for language proficiency. Yet we offer this for a fraction of the cost of a university, plus, best of all: no grades.  Languages are back to being fun, and PassionClass is more than just learning; it's a platform for sharing, exchanging, and experiencing the essence of language.  �
PassionClass is also the best place on the internet to learn new skills.  Want to learn to bake?  Do it here.  Want to learn an instrument?  Get started right away.  Want to share the way you became a chess grandmaster?  On PassionClass, you can use your creativity to teach what you’re most passionate about.  The collaborative nature of our classes not only enhances learning but also makes it a more socially enriching experience- while also saving you money.
PassionClass is also a leading platform in the realm of creative arts, providing an unmatched opportunity for individuals to explore and cultivate their artistic talents. Whether aspiring painters, musicians, or writers, PassionClass offers a vibrant space where creators can hone their craft under the guidance of experienced instructors. Group classes in creative arts foster a supportive environment where learners can receive feedback, collaborate with peers, and draw inspiration from diverse perspectives. By combining passion with expertise, PassionClass empowers individuals to unleash their creativity, express themselves authentically, and embark on a transformative journey of artistic discovery. 
But perhaps the most valuable aspect of PassionClass is the sense of community it fosters. Learning is inherently social, and our platform provides a space for like-minded individuals to connect, collaborate, and support each other.  PassionClass is where you'll find your group: if they’re in a class because they care, then you share interests and maybe a natural connection.
A personal tutor can cost $25, $50, $100 or more per hour.  By sharing the cost of instruction on PassionClass, individuals can access high-quality learning experiences at a fraction of the price they would pay for one-on-one sessions, while teachers make real money. Plus, reviews of classes let you know whether a class is good or great before you book.  This efficient allocation of resources enables PassionClass to offer a wider variety of courses while keeping classes affordable. Additionally, group environments foster peer interaction and collaborative learning, enhancing the overall educational experience. In essence, group classes at PassionClass make quality education accessible to a broader audience, promoting lifelong learning and personal development.

name: SAGLY
businessDescription: SAGLY helps mountain biker with their bike settings and maintenance.
longBusinessDescription:
Passion for mountain biking and innovation became SAGLY - a mobile app for suspension adjustment and bike maintenance
About ourselves as Founder
Anton Hörl and Mario Kemetinger, the two passionate mountain bikers and product developers behind SAGLY, met at a young age while mountain biking. At that time, the sport wasn't that popular and the scene in the region was even smaller. Anton and Mario, both of whom grew up in Leogang, live for the sport of mountain biking. Back then, Anton had never adjusted his mountain bike suspension settings correctly. Mario always helped him with the maintenance and adjustment of the mountain bike.
In addition to mountain biking in the Leogang bike park and in the dirt park they built themselves, which was in a friend's garden, they also founded a "film crew" with 2 other friends, the "Lahnvalley Crew". With this film crew they created videos and photos of themself mountain biking.
Many videos and photos were produced and successfully distributed on the web. The scene and the sponsors liked the produced videos, with which the Lahnvalley Crew reached a total of over 1 million viewers online. More and more sponsors were added, such as Alpinestars, SCOTT Sports, MAXXIS Tires and Bikepark Leogang. So they were able to finance their hobby a little out of their own pockets. Anton's settings on the bike also got better and better, thanks to Mario's tips.
Mountain bike trips were also financed in this way, including to the mountain bike mecca of Whistler in British Columbia, Canada. Other successful Lahnvalley Crew videos and photos were also created there.
After a while, working life became more and more important. But mountain biking remained a hobby. Both made their way into the IT industry.
How about a mobile app to improve my suspension setup?
This is how the SAGLY project was born, because the passion for the sport was still there. In his home office, Anton worked on new product ideas with a view of the Leogang bike park at home. He then sent Mario a message about what he thought of developing an app to find the ideal mountain bike suspension setting. Of course, Mario was enthusiastic about the idea and the project started.
The two find it very exciting to bring technology and innovation into sport. Mario, who has knowledge about mountain bike suspension settings, and Anton, who has software development skills, complement each other perfectly in the project and in August 2021 the first SAGLY version will be available in the app stores. Since then, the app has been continuously developed with user feedback.
Why use SAGLY?
Mountain bikes are equipped with suspension elements, some of which are associated with quite complex settings.
Most mountain bikers have often not optimally adjusted the suspension parts and thus have less riding fun and also endanger their safety. The maintenance of the mountain bike is also often neglected and this also results in more costs.
This is exactly why Anton and Mario developed SAGLY. SAGLY helps to finally document, improve and compare mountain bike settings in one place with other riders. The mobile app SAGLY also helps with mountain bike maintenance.
Beside a clear interface where you all of your settings are saved, there is also
an AI algorithm, SAG Guide, tire air pressure calculator that makes it easy to create a good basic setup. Based on physique, these guides suggest bike settings. All matching parts that the rider has on the bike can also be created. Finally, there is a balance test, with which the user can determine whether his suspension is balanced between the suspension fork and damper. Thus, the user has a good basic setup, which is half the battle when it comes to the settings on the bike.
From the basic setup, every mountain bike can then improve the setup at will. The WHAT SHOULD I DO, WHEN... guide gives the user assistance to further improve the setup with the help of SAGLY and their own assessment. SAGLY should by no means be a tool that strictly tells mountain bikers how to adjust their bike. It should help him much more to develop a feeling for his chassis and to find an individual setup based on his own assessment. The FEEDBACK LOOP also helps with this. With this function you can give SAGLY feedback on how you feel about the suspension after the last changes. Recommendations for further adjustments are then given on request. This feature is perhaps a little reminiscent of the bracketing method. This method is used by mountain bike World Cup riders. It basically guides the rider to a great setting by leading him in a certain direction (i.e. clockwise or counterclockwise) by changing a specific setting on the suspension until a point is found for the respective setting at which the rider feels good about the bike.
Many terms related to mountain bike suspension are explained in a comprehensible way and with the EXPLORE SETUPS function you can also find other riders' bikes and thus get inspiration of other riders suspension setups and their weight or riding style for good comparison. The suspension settings of other riders can also be tried out and copied into their own setups.
In addition, SAGLY is compatible with Strava, so the user can keep an overview of the mileage of the bike and upcoming maintenance. You can easily specify maintenance intervals in the basic setup, which provide the basis for this feature. Through the connection to the Strava account, the mileage or riding hours of the bike are always kept up to date. The progress bars show how long it is until the next maintenance. When maintenance is reached, you will receive a notification from SAGLY so that you do not forget to carry out the maintenance.
The HISTORY completes the feature package. Every change to the setup, every added feedback as well as every maintenance or every Strava ride is saved in the HISTORY. This helps to get an overview of the chassis changes or the maintenance that has been carried out or is due.
With SAGLY, mountain bikers have a tool in their pocket that they can use to get better at biking overall.
You can not only save the suspension settings in SAGLY and compare them with other riders, SAGLY offers much more. A wealth of features paired with an intuitive user interface should help every mountain biker to have more riding fun, more safety and more performance on the bike. Of course, SAGLY should also motivate every rider to show more love for the bike through maintenance and cleaning, thus saving money and preventing serious repairs and damage.
With these advantages, the founders are convinced that SAGLY should be on every mountain biker's smartphone.
Because not only beginners, but also advanced riders, SAGLY helps to get more out of the bike and thus become a better mountain bike rider.
Why are the two founders working on SAGLY?
For Anton and Mario, mountain biking is not just a sport, hobby or lifestyle. We associate mountain biking with much more.
When mountain biking you experience nature, improve your physical and mental health, get to know other people, feel joy and pleasure, strengthen your will and sometimes learn to get up again.
These are just some of the reasons the two think it's worth working on an innovative mobile app like SAGLY.
SAGLY technology not only helps you adjust and maintain the mountain bike, but also to experience a passion, mountain biking.
Who uses SAGLY and who is the app for?
More than 30,000 passionate mountain bikers are now using the app all over the world. Mountain bikers with hardtails but also full-suspension bikes use the app. And no matter if you are a beginner, advanced or professional, the app offers added value for all skill levels. Beginners benefit in particular from the explanations of the sometimes complicated mountain bike suspension know-how and from the guides for the initial suspension adjustment.
For beginners and advanced users, the functions WHAT SHOULD I DO, WHEN... or the FEEDBACK LOOP or the HISTORY help to improve the suspension setup to meet their own needs and to constantly improve it.
The maintenance feature helps riders of all skill levels extend bike life and save money.
Even professionals or semi-professionals benefit from the app and help with the implementation of the bracketing method on the suspension setup.
App details and prices
SAGLY is available in German and English and PRO features can be activated for an annual (€20) or monthly fee (€2.50). One week test version and basic features such as offline capability, the storage of one bike setup, the EXPLORE SETUPS feature or basic know-how as well as solutions to problems with your setup are available free of charge. SAGLY is available on Apple iOS and Android devices.

name: COOLIN
businessDescription: Coolin is a cutting-edge sustainable cooling system handling temperature-controlled logistics for transporting and storing temperature-sensitive goods. Leveraging IoT technology, Coolin ensures precise temperature regulation, reducing environmental impact and costs while enhancing product integrity throughout the supply chain. With its unique features and adaptability, Coolin is poised to transform the way industries such as food, pharmaceuticals, cosmetics, and chemicals manage their cold chain standard parcel logistics.
longBusinessDescription:
Coolin is a state-of-the-art sustainable cooling system designed to address the challenges of temperature-controlled logistics in transporting and storing temperature-sensitive goods for standard parcel logistics. Traditional methods of cooling, such as refrigerated transport and storage, are not only expensive but also environmentally harmful. Coolin offers a disruptive solution by leveraging IoT technology to optimize temperature regulation processes, reducing energy consumption, and minimizing carbon footprint.
At the core of Coolin's technology is its ability to maintain a defined temperature window during transportation and storage, ensuring the integrity and freshness of perishable goods. Whether it's food products like meat, fish, fruits, or pharmaceuticals such as vaccines, tablets, or serums, Coolin provides a reliable and eco-friendly solution to meet the stringent requirements of various industries.
One of Coolin's key features is its sustainability aspect. By enabling temperature-controlled transport through standard parcel logistics, Coolin eliminates the need for specialized refrigerated vehicles, reducing costs and carbon emissions. Additionally, Coolin utilizes refillable and environmentally safe chemicals, further minimizing its environmental impact.
Intelligence is another hallmark of Coolin's technology. With on-demand temperature regulation, Coolin's system initiates and regulates cooling processes only when necessary, optimizing energy usage and ensuring efficient operation. Moreover, Coolin's electronic monitoring system collects real-time data on temperature, humidity, and acceleration, providing comprehensive quality assurance for transported goods.
Coolin is not only sustainable and intelligent but also highly customizable to meet the specific needs of different industries and applications. Its adaptability allows for seamless integration into existing logistics infrastructure, making it a versatile solution for companies looking to optimize their cold chain logistics.
In summary, Coolin represents a paradigm shift in temperature-controlled logistics, offering a sustainable, intelligent, and customizable solution to meet the evolving needs of modern supply chains. With its innovative technology and commitment to sustainability, Coolin is poised to revolutionize the way temperature-sensitive goods are transported and stored, driving efficiency, reducing costs, and minimizing environmental impact.

businessDescription:

With myCulture, we're developing an app that provides users with personalised recommendations for art exhibitions – based on their interests. Like Netflix for art. That way, they receive a quick overview over relevant exhibitions and can directly book their museum ticket. With Digital Natives, museums reach a new target group and they can re-engage with them after their visit.

We’ve built a community of +2000 art lover of which over 130 have already signed up for our app pre-launch. We’re currently in talks with 40 museums in Vienna out of which 10 have already signed a contract with us. 

For each ticket sold, museums pay a transaction fee of 15 %. App users receive incentives that are connected to a point system.
This is part of our referral strategy which, in combination with social media, PR and partnerships, will generate 6,000 bookings in the first year.

myCulture combines the best of event calendars, booking platforms and personalised travel guides.
And there is more to come. New features, new markets and we're not limiting ourselves to visual arts but also want to expand into other cultural segments like theatre, opera and cabaret.

myCulture was founded and is managed by Vera L. B. Grablechner, a serial entrepreneur, business consultant and marketing expert with a passion for arts & culture. She's supported by a team of tech and creative talents as well as a strong advisory board with Sergiu Ardelean (Founder & CEO at Artivive) and Reanne Leuning (Director Creative Industries at Advantage Asutria).

App development and marketing costs for the app launch are covered by public funding and own funds. To scale our business, we are seeking an investment of 300,000 euros.

name: Lignovations
businessDescription: Lignovations, a spin-off from Vienna University of Technology, has developed a patented process to manufacture ‘Colloidal Lignin Particles’ (CLP) from biomass lignin. Lignovations innovative CLPs can serve as a platform material to replace many non-renewable ingredients that are harmful to human health and the environment such as UV filters, antioxidants, antimicrobials and emulsifiers. Due to its high performance and cleanliness, Lignovations material can be used in many high value applications such as cosmetics and coatings.
longBusinessDescription:
Many consumer products such as cosmetics, coatings and packaging cannot be produced without oil-based ingredients that are harmful to the environment and human health. Therefore, end product manufacturers encounter increasing pressure by consumers and regulators to increase the sustainability of their products. However, for many synthetic ingredients that fulfil important functionalities such as UV filters, antioxidants and emulsifiers natural alternatives are either non-existent or offer poor performance.
Lignovations has developed a patented process to manufacture natural functional ingredients from biomass (lignin) to replace harmful substances in high-value applications such as cosmetics, enabling manufacturers to improve their products. Our proprietary process enables the production of extremely small lignin particles which results in higher performance than other natural alternatives. Further, our particles are multifunctional and fully biodegradable.

name: Noreja
businessDescription: At Noreja we rethink process mining and place the business objects along the process at the center of attention. Therefore, we focus on target- and user-oriented visualizations which provide direct implications for action. A new way to conduct data integration combines domain knowledge of process experts with process data. An approach we call Causal Process Mining. Our software solution enables companies to leverage existing data from e.g., ERP, SCM, CRM, PLM or BPMS in order to transfer Business Process Management from subjective and time-consuming to data-driven and automated. Our solution differentiates itself from other offerings because it is tailored to avoid spaghetti-like diagrams. Instead, the focus is on the causal relationships between events and actionable insights that provide opportunities for process optimization. To this end, we provide a workflow-like procedure for analysts to identify anomalies and optimization potential without the need to understand process modeling notations or process mining specialties. We also support management with business critical Process Performance Indicators and decision-supporting visualizations.
tags: Data Mining, Information Technology, SaaS, Software

name: blackshark.ai
businessDescription: creating a digital twin of planet earth I powered by satellite data & artificial intelligence
tags: Artificial intelligence, Earth observation, Computer vision, Autonomous driving
longBusinessDescription:
blackshark.ai provides powerful insights into the world by extracting information from satellite imagery fully automatically. A scalable artificial intelligence builds the core of the blackshark platform, detecting features with incredible precision and speed. A novel machine learning approach was developed to train a neural network for new features rapidly, enabling blackshark to serve various use cases in many different industries.
Input sources supported:
- satellite imagery
- 2D photographs (aerial, street level, ...)
- point clouds (photogrammetry or lidar)
- HD map data
- OSM
- & more
Examples for feature detection:
- buildings (footprint, height, type, roof, orientation, facade)
- vegetation
- streets
- land classification
- flood detection
- & more
blackshark.ai can also fully automatically and semantically reconstruct detected features in 3D, using a patented technology for efficiently storing and streaming petabytes of data.
blackshark.ai is a team of 50+ data scientists, geospatial engineers, 3D rendering programmers and developers, self-funded and based in San Francisco, US, and Graz, Austria, Europe's computer vision hub.
We are on a mission to answer questions such as:
- Can my drone land in this backyard?
- How many solar panels are installed in India?
- How many tents does a certain refugee camp have?
- How many cars are parked in a specific parking lot?
What would you like to know?

longBusinessDescription:

ACTIVE COATING is odorless and colorless and works only with the help
of light. This means that both artificial and natural light activates window panes to attract and dissolve

name: Circe BioTech
businessDescription: Using ancient fermentation techniques - reinvented - we turn natural gas into food, feed and biodegradable plastics
longBusinessDescription:
Circe is a Transformative energy technology, using natural gas to produce sustainable plastics food and feed at industrial scale. Our process is copied from nature; decaying fish and plant leaves collect at the bottom of lakes, and eventually start releasing methane which are eaten by bacteria as they bubble up towards the surface. The bacteria form small protein clumps in their cells which are the natural nutrient feed source for the wild fish. Circular, sustainable protein made from natural gas, (methane) – nature´s cycle and the technological core of Circe´s biomimicry process. 
Natural gas is the cleanest burning fossil fuel and safe extraction and usage techniques have been developed over almost two centuries of extraction experience. Circe is however never complacent and works tirelessly to ensure that the methane, a greenhouse gas, is examined, controlled, and managed at all points of the inbound and processing stages. This is vital as our business´s positive impact on seven of the United Nations Sustainability Goals are the fundamental drivers behind our start up vision and why we do what we do. 
Circe´s bioreactors are a technological baseline for gas to value solutions using fermentation and have potential application beyond our initial protein targets. Using protein suppression techniques our scientists have been able to develop a process to make the biopolymer PHB (polyhydroxybutyrate) from methane using methanotrophic bacteria. At its most simple level, this is a gas to plastics solution, a polypropylene substitute, but with a huge added advantage of being biodegradable, also in difficult environments like the sea. Combined with the potential to save our oceans from unnecessary overfishing and all the associated oceanic issues of industrial trawling, our humble fermentation technology could eradicate the growing floating plastic islands in our precious waters. 
Circe is currently designing its first 5,000 litre bioreactor, from which just two more scale jumps will bring us to our final 50,000 litre proof of industrialisation, deployment Q2´23. Multiple units in series will create the first Circe Mega Site in 2024 which will produce 25,000 tonnes of protein per year which if fully substituted for fishmeal would allow 600 million more fish to carry on living in the sea, or prevent the usage of 10,000 hectares of deforested land, every single year.

tags: tinnitus, health tech, medical devices, doctors, hearing aids, audiologists, healthcare, medical
longBusinessDescription: Cleanhearing is a hearing solutions company and the manufacturer of Sono, a medical device and multimodal system for tinnitus relief that combines tinnitus-specific electrical stimulation technology with a tailored notched music therapy. Sono’s specialised headphones and handheld controller deliver pulses of electromagnetic energy over the auditory cortex and temporal regions of the brain to target the physiological causes of tinnitus. Patients can use Sono as a standalone treatment, or connect Sono to their smartphone and the Cleanhearing app for a second, complementary tailored notched music therapy.  Sono’s patented technology was developed according to scientific research into effects of pulsed electromagnetic fields and notched music on tinnitus perception and underlying tinnitus pathophysiology. It was developed by European engineers with support from leading medical colleges in the US and Japan. In 2019, Cleanhearing was a global finalist at Falling Wall Ventures competition for science startups.

Limited mobility. Unlimited travel. 

We all want to see the world, and roomchooser aims to make that easily possible for people with limited mobility. Breaking down barriers and opening up accessible travel, roomchooser intends to take the hassle out of booking accessible hotel rooms.
longBusinessDescription:
About roomchooser
THE SPIRIT OF ADVENTURE. We all want to see the world, and roomchooser aims to make that easily possible for people with limited mobility. Breaking down barriers and opening up accessible travel, roomchooser intends to take the hassle out of booking accessible hotel rooms. We are embarking on a quest to unlock your adventurous spirit, by becoming your one stop shop for accessible hotel room and travel bookings across the globe.
EFFORTLESS TRAVEL PLANS. Planning a trip is time-consuming for anyone and in particular for a person with limited mobility. You will often have to compromise along the way, and the tedious process can even ruin the excitement of travel and planning.
At roomchooser we aim to put the fun back into your journey. We like you to worry about the unmissable sights you want to see and the local cuisine you want to devour, and not about whether your hotel room really meets your accessibility needs.
Booking with roomchooser means that what you see is what you get. Leveraging our partner network, we check the room and take pictures of room and hotel facilities to avoid nasty surprises when you arrive at your destination. We aim to add information on key features as well as inspire you to explore the world.
WE'VE LEARNED FROM EXPERIENCE. Our intrepid founder Michael knows all about the drawbacks of traveling as a person with limited mobility. Adventuring across the world, he has experienced all the difficulties of finding the right hotel room - from the pitfalls to the unexpected surprises. In a bid to simplify the process and open up the travel industry to everyone, roomchooser was born.
We not only aim to list accessible rooms across the globe, but we are committed to working with the hospitality and travel industry in order to improve their accessibility and to create further travel opportunities for people with limited mobility.
Room by room, we are changing the way you travel across the world.

Real time alerts are sent to you, your veterinarian or caregiver via smart phone, SMS and email  at the first signs of life threatening disorders such as colic, stall casting and foaling.
longBusinessDescription:
Despite their size and power, horses are fragile animals that tend to die prematurely of undetected disorders, diseases and self-inflicted injuries even in the safety of their own stall. 10 to 11 percent of the equine population suffers from colic each year, which is the number one cause of death in adult horses and the primary reason for emergency medical intervention and that in most cases strikes in the middle of the night when the horse is left unattended. In the EU and U.S. alone there are 1.7 million cases of colic reported every year, of which 7 percent will face life threatening complications. The value of horses lost to colic in the U.S. is assessed at $70 million with the total cost to the industry is estimated at $144 million p.a. In the EU, the cost to the industry is estimated at 245 million.
Currently, there are no effective monitoring solutions on the market to protect the welfare of horses today. Horse owners and care givers are unable to monitor the wellness of their horse 24x7. Regular visits by the horse owner together with routine veterinary inspection is currently the only way to monitor horses today. While it is generally accepted that most equine disorders and diseases can be successfully treated if early veterinary intervention is sought, veterinarians (let alone owners) currently have no instrument to monitor sick or injured horses in real time.
